modules.description: This module offers arithmetic operations (addition, multiplication, division) and bitwise manipulations (XOR, shift, AND) on 32-bit integers, along with register-move functions like `mov` for low-level data handling. It supports both register-to-register and register-to-immediate variants, enabling precise control over integer values in virtual machine or assembly-like environments. Specific use cases include optimizing numerical computations and managing register states in compiled or interpreted execution contexts.

Checks if the packet data pointed to by register R1 is an ARP packet by inspecting the Ethernet header. Operates on raw byte sequences and network protocol headers. Used to filter or process network traffic in eBPF programs running in the kernel.

This module offers arithmetic and bitwise operations such as addition, multiplication, XOR, and shifts, supporting both register-to-register and register-integer interactions. It manipulates register values and integer literals, enabling precise control over low-level data transformations. Use cases include optimizing compiler intermediate representations or implementing virtual machine instructions requiring bit-level manipulation.
